Germany, Saxony, August I, 1553-1586, AR Taler, dated 1576, 28.78g

orb AVGVSTVS D G DVX SAXO SA ROMA IMP,

HB ARCHIMARS CHAL ET ELEC,

coat (shield) of arms, containing crossed swords,

lions, and eagles; above, 3 crested helmets

Dav. 9798

Posted March 2017

Germany (German States), Saxony, "Three Brothers", AR Thaler, dated 1593

orb CHRISTIAN IOHAN GEORG ET AVGVSTVS,

armored(?) busts of Christian, John George, and August, facing, 1593/

HB FRAT ET DV CES SAXON,

coat (shield) of arms, containing crossed swords, lions, eagles,

and chicken(?) (or duck?); above, 3 crested helmets

Dav. 9820

Posted March 2017

Germany, Saxony, Christian I, Johann Georg, and August, 1601-1611,

AR Half Taler, dated 1608, 12.89g

orb CHRISTIAN II D G S R I ARCHIM E EL,

armored bust (of Christian?), holding sword, 1608; below,

coat (shield) of arms, containing crossed swords/

IOHAN GEORG ET AVGVST IR ETD SHR, armored busts

(of Johann Georg and August?); below, coat (shield) of arms

Kohl. 102

Posted March 2017

Germany, Saxony, Johann George and August, 1611-1615, AR Taler, dated 1613, 28.81g

orb IOHAN GEORG D G SA RO IMP ARCHIM ELE,

armored bust (of Johann George?), holding sword; suit of armor with crested

helmet; 1613; below, coat (shield) of arms, containing crossed swords/

E AVGVST F E D S I C E M,

armored(?) bust (of August?); around, 18 coats (shields) of arms,

containing lions, daggers, eagle, duck(?) (or goose?), etc.

Car. 7573

Posted March 2017

Germany, Saxony, Freidrich August III, 1763-1827, AR Medal, dated 1764, from Oexlein, 46 mm, 21.84g

TRINVM GRATIOSVM,

3 Graces ("Grazien") standing, holding lockets depicting: Maria Antonias from Bayern,

the prince, and his Uncle Xaver, the sponsor of the "Retablissements"

in Saxony; below, coat (shield) of arms, containing crossed swords/

ASPICE VENTVRO LAETENTVRVT OMNIA SAECLO MDCCLXIIII,

Pax standing in flourishing countryside (landscape), holding caduceus and

cornucopia; in background, trees, animals, bridge, church, and building

Slg. Engelhardt 1666

Posted March 2017
